query topics + store topics in
│
│── adaptive params (computed once from store data, not per query)
│   filter_min_ancestor_ic = p25(store ICs)
│   ic_weight_alpha = query_ic_mean / max_store_ic, clamped [0.1, 0.9]
│   ic_prune_ratio = p10/p50(store ICs), clamped [0.1, 0.9]
│   sibling_ic_ratio = p25/p75(store ICs), clamped [0.1, 0.95]
│   use_idf = entropy(IDF) > 0.3
│
│── pass 1: topic gate (speed optimization, not a hard gate)
│   step 1: query centroid × all store centroids (one matmul)
│     sort scores, gap_split: find biggest gap, everything above admitted
│   step 2: CUI overlap rescue
│     excluded topics that share an exact CUI with query → admitted
│   step 3: fallback
│     zero admitted? score ALL topics in pass 2 (never miss for speed)
│
│   before pass 2: precompute ancestors for admitted doc CUIs (8 hops)
│   include topic_cui in matchable set
│
│── pass 2: score each admitted topic (3 signals, no thresholds on any)
│
│   signal 1: cui_ratio
│     for each query CUI, check against all topic CUIs:
│       try exact match → credit = 1.0, stop
│       try parent-child (8-hop BFS) → credit = IC(parent)/IC(child), stop
│       try MICA → credit = Lin score, stop
│       nothing → 0
│     cui_ratio = sum(credits) / n_query_CUIs
│
│   signal 2: vec_sim
│     dot(query centroid, topic centroid)
│     one number, no CUI-level comparison
│
│   signal 3: lin_avg
│     only for query CUIs that cui_ratio couldn't match
│     for each: compute Lin against every topic CUI, keep best
│     Lin(A,B) = 2 * IC(MICA) / (IC(A) + IC(B))
│     MICA = most specific shared ancestor
│     average the best scores
│
│   why three: "fever and chills" → cui_ratio carries it
│              "worsening condition" → vec_sim carries it (no CUI overlap)
│              "OA of left knee" → lin_avg carries it (parent-child hierarchy)
│
│── pass 3: z-score normalization
│   per signal across all candidates: z = (value - mean) / std
│   final score = z_cui + z_vec + z_lin, shifted to [0, 1]
│   highest-variance signal auto-dominates, no manual weights
│   all flat → fallback w_cui=0.40, w_vec=0.30, w_lin=0.30
│
│── pass 4: relative threshold
│   threshold = best_score * 0.40 (score_ratio)
│   score_min = 0.01 (structural floor, catches float artifacts)
│   zero-evidence guard: suppress only if all 3 signals = 0.0
│   no per-signal thresholds, no fixed result count
│
│── LLM reasoning (optional)
│   top results → gemini with matched CUIs + topic labels + chunk text
│   verdict: good/partial/poor + explanation
│
└── out: ranked document chunks above threshold
